and considered one of the Seven Wonders of Nature,
as well as the El Nido Reserve and the Coron island. Rep. Acosta presented the ff. suggestions to help maximize the tourism potentials of Palawan and the City of Puerto Princesa...: 1) a policy program to expand and intensify secondary attractions and projects that must be supported by the national government; 2) a plan or program to improve infrastructure facilities in Palawan such as a cruise port facility that could cater to tourists and visitors; and 3) a measure 
declaring Palawan as the ecological tourism capital of the Philippines. (SOURCE: House Journal No. 22,pp.11-12)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ACOSTA, GIL P.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-09-14</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Speech-Privilege Hour</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TOURISM ON 2016-09-21</td></tr></table>